@model NMoneys.Web.Models.ApiRequest

@{
	ViewBag.Title = "nMoneys";
	Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<section class="container">
	<article>
		<h2><a id="Api"></a>An Api?<a href="#Api"></a></h2>
		<p>
			Nowadays, if you do not provide some sort of REST-y/Web-ish/JSON-able API, you are not <em>in</em>.<br />
			And so, <em>NMoneys</em> provides a very simple web api.
		</p>
	</article>
	<hr />
	<article>
		<h2><a id="Content"></a>What's in the Api?<a href="#Content"></a></h2>
		<p>Amongst the (still) limited capabilities of the api are:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Getting an subset of all the currencies that are supported.</li>
			<li>Get extended information about single currencies.</li>
			<li>Formatting numeric quantities.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>But, instead of me telling you&hellip;</p>
	</article>
	<hr />
	<article>
		<h2>Want to use it?</h2>
		<p>&hellip; why not requesting an API key?.<br/>They are free and, trust me, I do not have any intention to spam you or sell your information. I promise.</p>
		@{
			Html.RenderPartial(Model.Requested ? "_requested" : "_requestForm", Model);
		}
	</article>
	<hr/>
	<article>
		<h2><a id="Doc"></a>Documentation<a href="#Doc"></a></h2>
		<p>&hellip; or why not diving into its documentation?</p>
		<ul class="nav nav-tabs">
			<li class="active"><a href="#apiary" data-toggle="tab">Apiary</a></li>
			<li><a href="#metadata" data-toggle="tab">Local Metadata</a></li>
			<li><a href="#swagger" data-toggle="tab">Swagger</a></li>
		</ul>
		<div class="tab-content">
			<div class="tab-pane active" id="apiary">
				Good-looking, interactive documentation is hosted in <a href="http://apiary.io/" target="_blank">Apiary</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;
				<a class="btn" href="http://docs.nmoneys.apiary.io" target="_blank">Check it out!</a>
			</div>
			<div class="tab-pane" id="metadata">
				Good-looking enough and definitely less interactive but equally useful is provided by <a href="http://www.servicestack.net/">ServiceStack</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;
				<div class="btn-group">
					<a class="btn" href="api/json/metadata?op=Currencies" target="_blank">Currencies</a>
					<a class="btn" href="api/json/metadata?op=Currency" target="_blank">Currency</a>
					<a class="btn" href="api/json/metadata?op=Format" target="_blank">Format</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="tab-pane" id="swagger">
				Very interactive <a href="https://github.com/wordnik/swagger-core">Swagger</a> documentation is on its way.
			</div>
		</div>
	</article>
	<hr/>
</section>

@section scripts
{
	@Scripts.Render("~/bundles/parsley")
	@Scripts.Render("~/bundles/app_api")
}
